.TH "ufshcd_read_string_desc" 9 "ufshcd_read_string_desc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ufshcd_read_string_desc \- read string descriptor
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ufshcd_read_string_desc
.BI "(struct ufs_hba *hba "  ","
.BI "u8 desc_index "  ","
.BI "u8 **buf "  ","
.BI "bool ascii "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hba" 12
pointer to adapter instance
.IP "desc_index" 12
descriptor index
.IP "buf" 12
pointer to buffer where descriptor would be read,
the caller should free the memory.
.IP "ascii" 12
if true convert from unicode to ascii characters
null terminated string.
.SH "RETURN"
*      string size on success.
*      -ENOMEM: on allocation failure
*      -EINVAL: on a wrong parameter
